main event: On November 11, 1966, a witness reported seeing a shiny metal cone with short wings in the sky over York, Pennsylvania.
interesting points: The sighting occurred outside the witness's home and was fleeting as the object disappeared behind houses., The witness noted a second sighting the following day around the same time., The object was described as being very shiny and cone-shaped., The witness estimated the object to be about an inch long when viewed from approximately 90 feet away., The report was forwarded to Project Blue Book for further evaluation.
sighted object: a shiny metal cone with short wings
witness description: the witness reported seeing the object while standing outside their home
